'Diphenyl disulfide' is the chemical compound with the formula
[C 6H 5S] 2. This colorless crystalline material
is often abbreviated Ph 2S 2. It is one of the most popular
organic disulfides used in organic synthesis. Minor contamination by thiophenol
is responsible for the disagreeable odour associated with this compound.
